cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a convolutional neural network for semantic image segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a generative model called conditional variational auto-encoder (CVAE), which involves learning high-level prior for semantic segmentation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses state-of-the-art fully convolutional network structure for the implementation of the encoders and decoder, which suggests that it may also belong to sub-categories related to neural networks and multimedia, such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
